{
  "texts": [
    "The p.d.f.s of these cases also exhibit overlapping tails with small p(δ e,1) values, suggesting that the probability of extreme errors (RMAE 40 % and R 2 0.75) is negligible.",
    "For the strongly forced wind waves (i.e.",
    "W1-16 case), however, the performance of the ML model slightly degrades, yielding a most probable relative error of δ e,1 ≈ 30 % with a coefficient of determination of R 2 ≈ 0.9.",
    "In this case, although the maximum relative error increases to 90 %, R 2 remains acceptable at around 0.55.",
    "The decrease in the model accuracy with increasing wind speed can be attributed to more frequent airflow separation events over wind waves and the increased signal-to-noise ratio in the experimental measurements."
  ]
}